	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64248708">The problem with air-source heat pumps is that they rapidly lose their heating power when it gets cold which is exactly when you need more heating power. While they may technically still be (barely) more efficient than gas or electric heating when it drops below -30C the reduction in their heating power means that you need a huge system that is vastly overpowered for most of the year.
<br> <br>
In northern climates like that you really need a ground source heat pump but these are a lot more expensive to install sin</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64248708">

