		<div id="comment_body_64247906"><p>&gt; you have to use some kind of non-water fluid</p><p>Not necessarily. You can also have the panels drain into a reservoir overnight, with the circulating pump only turning on again in the morning once the panels have gotten warmer than the reservoir.  Why have fluid in the panels when there's no heat to be collected?</p><p>A DIY system I've occasionally considered building: <a href="https://www.builditsolar.com/Projects/SpaceHeating/DHWplusSpace/Main.htm" title="builditsolar.com">https://www.builditsolar.com/P...<span class="substr"> </span></a> [builditsolar.com] </p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64247906">

