	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64247936"><p>The great thing about heat is that water is actually a *really* cheap and easy way to store a LOT of it.</p><p>Most solar water heated systems I've seen store at least 5-10 days worth of heat - after all it only costs you the price of an insulated water tank. Unlike electric batteries, it's easy to budget for the a worst-case scenario.</p><p>Heck, I know one guy that has a huge enough tank that he stores heat in the summer to heat his house through the winter.</p></div>
	</div>

